{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Use British English|date=August 2017}} '''Natasha Raskin-Sharp''' (born in 1986 in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]]) is a [[Scottish people|Scottish]] antiques and art expert, especially in Scottish contemporary art, best known for her appearances on television. The daughter of contemporary Scottish artist [[Philip Raskin]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.holroydgallery.co.uk/raskin/philip.htm |title=Holroyd Gallery and Picture Framer, Scotland |website=Holroydgallery.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref> she has appeared in programmes in the UK and the USA including ''[[Antiques Road Trip]]'', ''[[Antiques Road Trip#Celebrity Antiques Road Trip|Celebrity Antiques Road Trip]]'', ''[[Flog It!]]'', ''[[Bargain Hunt]]'', ''[[For What It's Worth (game show)|For What It's Worth]]'' and ''[[Baggage Battles]]''.<ref name="mctears1">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.mctears.co.uk/departments/contact.aspx?id=30e31f08-c03c-4c88-8820-909f998f4cfd |title=Meet McTear's: Natasha Raskin &#124; McTear's Auctioneers, Glasgow |website=Mctears.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref>
==Early life and education== She was born in 1986 in [[Glasgow]], the middle of three children in a family of art lovers and collectors.<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/5VTxQqNTjhNRqkkCP9cpMXW/natasha-raskin |title=BBC One - Bargain Hunt - Natasha Raskin |website=Bbc.co.uk |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref> Her father is the artist Philip Raskin. Initially she studied law but left her degree course after a year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundaypost.com/in10/when-tv-came-calling-natasha-raskin-had-a-dirty-secret-to-confess-2/ |title=When TV came calling, Natasha Raskin had a secret to confess |publisher=Sunday Post |date= |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref>
==Career== After deciding that law was not for her, she undertook a number of activities, during which she had a placement with the [[Alice Temperley]] fashion house,<ref name="Bill Gibb">{{cite web|author=Bill Gibb |url=https://www.sundaypost.com/in10/entertainment/my-favourite-holiday-natasha-raskin-loved-her-time-in-america-working-on-the-obama-campaign-but-the-danube-is-her-ideal-destination/ |title=Natasha Raskin loved her time working with Barack Obama |website=Sundaypost.com |date= |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref> and worked in the primary elections of 2008 for [[Barack Obama]] in [[New Hampshire]], during which he referred to her as part of "the Scottish contingent" of his team, and provided her with a signed reference for her work.<ref name="Bill Gibb"/>
After returning to [[Glasgow University]] to gain a degree in the History of Art and French,<ref name="mctears1"/> she joined Glasgow auction house McTear's, as an auctioneer and latterly as Head of Pictures, dealing mainly with Scottish contemporary art.<ref name="autogenerated1"/> After her marriage, she now shares her auctioneering and valuation event duties at McTear's with her TV career.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.sundaypost.com/in10/entertainment/natasha-raskin-never-busy-five-tv-shows-juggle/ |title=Natasha Raskin has never been so busy with FIVE TV shows to juggle |publisher=Sunday Post |date= |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref>
===Television=== Raskin is a regular expert contributor on the BBC's ''[[Antiques Road Trip]]'', ''[[Antiques Road Trip#Celebrity Antiques Road Trip|Celebrity Antiques Road Trip]]'', ''[[Flog It!]]'' and has acted as both expert and lead presenter on BBC's ''[[Bargain Hunt]]''. She appeared in the US show ''[[Baggage Battles]]''. Her most recent show is ''[[For What It's Worth (game show)|For What It's Worth]]'' with [[Fern Britton]].<ref name="mctears1"/> She has also appeared on the Janice Forsyth Show on [[BBC Radio Scotland]], reviewing an exhibition at the [[National Galleries of Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0760hvk |title=BBC Radio Scotland - The Janice Forsyth Show, Nieves in session, plus the Tuesday Review |website=Bbc.co.uk |date=2016-04-19 |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref> She has been a guest presenter on [[BBC Radio Scotland]]'s ''The Music Match'', and since 2017, has presented a weekly programme, playing an eclectic mix of music. <ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b074zymc |title=BBC Radio Scotland - The Music Match, Natasha Raskin |website=Bbc.co.uk |date=2016-04-01 |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref> She has presented story segments for ''[[The One Show]]'' on BBC 1.
